By Steve Agbota           The Managing Director of National Inland Waterways Authority (NIWA), Chief George Moghalu has congratulated the newly confirmed Minister of Transportation, Engr. Mu’azu Sambo and the new Minister of State for Transportation, Mr. Ademola Adewole Adegoroye. Moghalu made this commendation on behalf of the Board, Management and entire staff of the Authority, via a press statement signed by the General Manager, Corporate Affairs, Mr. Jibril Darda’u. The press statement read: “NIWA wishes to warmly join Nigerians in celebrating and congratulating Engr. Mu’azu Jaji Sambo, on his meritorious appointment as the newly confirmed Minister of Transportation and Mr. Ademola Adewole Adegoroye as the Minister of State for Transportation. “Indeed the both appointments by His Excellency, President Muhammadu Buhari GCFR is a clear testimony and recognition of their competence, hard work, dedication, and sterling track records of achievements in their previous national assignments,” he said. The NIWA Managing Director further stated that he strongly believed that both Ministers will bring their wealth of experience, wisdom and knowledge to bear in the discharge of their new assignments by improving the affairs of the Ministry.